$\overline{z}$ 
\emph{before} calling \texttt{covar}.

\section{\texttt{median}: the median}

\subsection{Use}
\iexec[quiet,trace,stdout=xtract.txt]{grep 'proc median' -A3 nstat.chpl}

\lstinputlisting[style=lstchapelf, numbers=none]{xtract.txt}



\subsection{Theory}

Calculates the median of the data in array $\vet{x}=(x_0,x_1,\ldots,x_{n-1})$.
The array is sorted by an index array $I$ such that $x_{I_0}$ is the
minimum value and $x_{I_{n-1}}$ is the maximum value. Returns
\begin{equation}
  x_{\text{median}} = \begin{cases}
    \frac{1}{2}\left( x_{I_{n/2-1}}+x_{I_{n/2}}\right) & \text{$n$ is even}, \\
    x_{I_{n/2}} & \text{$n$ is odd}.
  \end{cases}
\end{equation}

The domain of \texttt{ax} \emph{does not have to start at 0}, because
\texttt{median} takes care to reindex it internally.

